# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IP Access Restriction — Template
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to use:
#   1. Copy this file to .htaccess (or rename it):
#      cp .htaccess.example .htaccess
#   2. Uncomment the Require ip line(s) for your network(s)
#      by removing the leading "# "
#   3. Apache requires AllowOverride All (or at minimum
#      AllowOverride AuthConfig) in the VirtualHost config
#      for .htaccess files to work.
#   4. Add more Require ip lines for additional subnets
#      (e.g., a corporate VPN).
#
# NOTE: In Apache 2.4+ just list Require ip directives.
# There's no need for <RequireAll> — Apache denies all
# by default, and Require ip creates exceptions.
# Incorrect: <RequireAll> Require all denied; Require ip ... </RequireAll>
# Correct:   Require ip <your_network>
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Require ip 192.168.111
# Require ip 10.0.0.0/8
# Require ip 172.16.0.0/12
